%% root main
%% AUTHORED FROM CODE — src/main.ts (composition root: builds ctx, instantiates initX modules in dependency order, wires ctx.hooks, boots).
%% main constructs the shared AppContext, then each core module as a factory over that context. Modules never import main; they read/write ctx and call back through ctx.hooks. Solid = main composes (construction order); dotted = a module reads a shared global or calls back through a hook.
%% --- composition root ---
%% fm:meta main name=main
%% fm:meta main desc=composition root; resolve DOM, build AppContext, loadPrefs, instantiate every initX in dependency order, wire ctx.hooks, then boot (apply theme, restore-or-seed, render, sync).
%% --- core container public contracts (placeholder; each fragment is canonical) ---
%% fm:meta context name=createHooks
%% fm:meta context desc=the shared conduit; AppContext is the one object every module reads, Hooks is the late-bound cross-module call table main fills after all init() run (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta state name=createState
%% fm:meta state desc=the model + all pure geometry/containment reads over it; owned and mutated through ctx.state (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta camera name=initCamera
%% fm:meta camera desc=pan/zoom transform + fit; reads state geometry, writes ctx.cam, calls drawMinimap/persist back through hooks (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta history name=initHistory
%% fm:meta history desc=undo/redo snapshot stack over the model; restore() re-runs render/sync/renderInspector through hooks (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta persistence name=initPersistence
%% fm:meta persistence desc=localStorage autosave + prefs load/save; debounced persist of model+camera, migrating frontmatter on load (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta validate name=validateModel
%% fm:meta validate desc=structural integrity + semantic round-trip diff over a model; pure, no DOM (fragment is canonical).
%% fm:meta frontmatter name=frontmatter
%% fm:meta frontmatter desc=node public-interface frontmatter; normalize, prune, (de)serialize to Mermaid, and type cross-reference (fragment is canonical).
%% --- shared globals (cross-container; canonical defs live here) ---
%% fm:meta types name=types
%% fm:meta types desc=shared domain vocabulary — DiagramNode, DiagramEdge, Frontmatter, Camera, Prefs and the enums. Pure types, imported almost everywhere.
%% fm:meta config name=config
%% fm:meta config desc=static registries + tiny escapers — SHAPES/KINDS tables, palette/themes/fonts, storage keys, zoom bounds, esc/escM. Read across every bucket.
%% fm:meta runtime name=createRuntime
%% fm:meta runtime desc=transient cross-layer UI state interaction owns and render reads — editingId, linkSrc, tracedType. Held on ctx.runtime; not persisted.
%% fm:meta seed name=seed
%% fm:meta seed desc=first-run sample diagram; one-shot model write used only when there is no autosave to restore.
%% --- shared types owned by one module but referenced as deps elsewhere ---
%% fm:meta CameraApi name=CameraApi
%% fm:meta CameraApi desc=camera's returned API surface (applyCam, toWorld, zoom*, persistSoon); consumed by minimap, nodes, layout, view, files, pointer, inline-edit.
%% fm:meta Issue name=Issue
%% fm:meta Issue desc=one validation finding — level (error/warn), machine code, message, and the node/edge ids it points at.
%% fm:meta TypeRef name=TypeRef
%% fm:meta TypeRef desc=a parsed "name: Type" frontmatter slot; the type part is the cross-reference identity.
